      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean, a lot of people are worried that these shifts don't just change policy, but actually threaten the \"cultural cohesion\" that keeps a democracy stable. some analysts argue that a rapid influx of different cultural values and different ways of thinking about governance can lead to a breakdown of the existing social contract. do you think there's a risk that these demographic changes could lead to a loss of the traditional western identity that these institutions were built on?",
